For the first time since I've been on the lake- it appears we had a major algae bloom. Hard to describe but I'll try. Very fine light green-moves through the water like smoke in the air. Does not float and rest at the surface. covering most areas 12 ft deep or less. Is this what is called- "the lake turned over"  Spoke to many elder lake residents. Some have seen it before but only a few times in past 20 years. Deeper areas like my Secchi guage location seem normal.
The algae bloom from last fall is now washing up on the north and west beaches. Very fine grayish green and very stinky.
I have never seen the lake this clear. the depth was confirmed by 2 other people in the boat with me
numerous boaters already on the lake. When I choose the water color as green- it is dark green not in any way a visible algae green
water was a little worked up by speedboats. It also rained most of the morning
water level continues to receed. estimated depth is down 4-5 ft from nov 2004
